#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A tiger has escaped from a property in the Walkerville area, South of Johannesburg. It is understood the animal escaped when the fences were cut Saturday night. It was then reported to have been sighted near the Daleside Vet and had attacked one person and killed a dog. Citizens are urged to be on high alert and not approach the tiger as it is aggressive and will attack without provocation. Watch the video above for more details on this story.